To install nbconvert from inside a Jupyter notebook code cell, use the following command:

!pip install nbconvert

The exclamation point (!) tells Jupyter to run it as a shell command, not Python code.

After installing, you can convert a .ipynb to:

  • PDF (.pdf)
  • HTML (.html)
  • Markdown (.md)
  • and others, using:
jupyter nbconvert DragonHawk_Playbook.ipynb --to pdf

or from a notebook code cell:

!jupyter nbconvert DragonHawk_Playbook.ipynb --to pdf

Pro Tips:

  • For PDF export, you'll need LaTeX installed (pdflatex). If it errors out, try HTML instead:

    !jupyter nbconvert DragonHawk_Playbook.ipynb --to html

  • To install LaTeX later:
